Up-regulated genes with Log2 fold change > 2.5

tables_UP <- list(
  all_20d = DEG20vsC_UP, 
  all_30d = DEG30vsC_UP, 
  `4x_20d` = DEG4x_20vsC_UP, 
  `4x_30d` = DEG4x_30vsC_UP, 
  `8x_20d` = DEG8x_20vsC_UP, 
  `8x_30d` = DEG8x_30vsC_UP)

tables_named <- lapply(names(tables_UP), function(name) {
  tables_UP[[name]] %>%
    select(IPR, log2FoldChange) %>%
    mutate(Condition = name)})

data_combined <- bind_rows(tables_named)

library(tibble)  # Load tibble for column_to_rownames()

data_wide <- data_combined %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Condition, values_from = log2FoldChange) 
data_wide <- as.data.frame(data_wide)

# Set IPR column as row names
rownames(data_wide) <- data_wide$IPR
data_wide <- data_wide[, -1]
data_wide[is.na(data_wide)] <- 0 
heatmap_matrix <- as.matrix(data_wide)

# Remove rows where all values are below 2.0
heatmap_matrix <- heatmap_matrix[apply(heatmap_matrix, 1, function(x) any(x >= 2.5)), ]
breaks <- seq(0, max(heatmap_matrix), length.out = 50)
color_palette <- colorRampPalette(c("white", "#DC3220"))(length(breaks) - 1)
column_order <- c("all_20d", "4x_20d", "8x_20d", "all_30d", "4x_30d", "8x_30d" )
heatmap_matrix <- heatmap_matrix[, column_order]

UP_heatmap<-pheatmap(
  heatmap_matrix, 
  cluster_rows = F, 
  cluster_cols = F, 
  color = color_palette,
  breaks = breaks,
  border_color = NA,  
  show_rownames = TRUE, 
  fontsize_number = 10,
  fontsize_row = 10,  
  display_numbers = TRUE,  
  number_format = "%.1f",
  clustering_distance_rows = "euclidean")
UP_heatmap

Down-regulated genes with Log2 fold change > 2.5

  tables_DOWN[[name]] %>%

    mutate(Condition = name)})

data_wide <- data_combined %>%

# Set IPR column as row names

# Remove rows where all values are below -2.5
heatmap_matrix <- heatmap_matrix[apply(heatmap_matrix, 1, function(x) any(x < -3)), ]

# Add the Log2FC for the IPR021562 (they are very high, but p-values were not calculated because of the big difference in Log2FC)
heatmap_matrix["IPR021562", "all_30d"] <- -34.9
heatmap_matrix["IPR021562", "4x_20d"] <- -2.8
heatmap_matrix["IPR021562", "8x_20d"] <- -27.3
heatmap_matrix["IPR021562", "8x_30d"] <- -26.7
heatmap_matrix["IPR021562", "4x_30d"] <- -31.6
color_palette <- colorRampPalette(c("#005AB5", "white"))(100)
breaks <- seq(min(heatmap_matrix), max(heatmap_matrix), length.out = 100)

column_order <- c("all_20d", "4x_20d", "8x_20d", "all_30d", "4x_30d", "8x_30d" )
heatmap_matrix <- heatmap_matrix[, column_order]

DOWN_heatmap<-pheatmap(
  heatmap_matrix, 
  cluster_rows = F, 
  cluster_cols = F, 
  color = color_palette,
  breaks = breaks,
  border_color = NA,

  fontsize_number = 10,
  fontsize_row = 10,  
  display_numbers = TRUE,  
  number_format = "%.1f",
  clustering_distance_rows = "euclidean")

Ploidy levels: up-regulated

data <- data.frame(gene = DEG8x_4x_c_UP$IPR, Log2FC = DEG8x_4x_c_UP$log2FoldChange)


heatmap_data <- data %>% column_to_rownames("gene") %>% as.matrix() 

Heatmap(
  heatmap_data,
  name = "Log2FC",                         # Title for the color legend
  row_names_gp = gpar(fontface = "italic"), # Italicize gene names
  col = colorRampPalette(c("white", "#117733"))(100), # Color gradient
  cluster_rows = FALSE,                    # Disable row clustering
  cluster_columns = FALSE,                 # Disable column clustering
  show_row_names = TRUE,                   # Show gene names
  show_column_names = FALSE,               # Hide column names
  cell_fun = function(j, i, x, y, width, height, fill) {
    grid.text(sprintf("%.1f", heatmap_data[i, j]), x, y, gp = gpar(fontsize = 10, col = "black")) })
